fields.area_description: Thanalan is the area surrounding Ul'dah, the Jewel of the Desert. It is split up into 5 different sections. These areas are largely barren, dry areas with sparse vegetation and little life to them. This has not stopped the various races from trying to set up outposts wherever they can, even if monsters constantly roam the lands nearby.

The Black Shroud is a dense forest that surrounds Gridania. It has been the home of the Elezen for generations, and they have used its bountiful lumber for crafting, while using the dense forest for their own protection from the outside world.

La Noscea is the marine region located in the south-eastern part of Eorzea, and Limsa Lominsa, one of the starting cities, is located in La Noscea.
The maritime metropolis is located in the south of the island Vylbrand that Aldenard precedes in the west, the Gulf of Rhotano.
Their patron deity is Llymlaen, the aerodrome controller, the goddess of seafarers.

Mor Dhona is an inland region of Eorzea, and the site of the first aerial battle in recorded history â€” a conflict that took place above Silvertear Lake. The air was filled with the deafening roars of cannons from magitek engines and dragonkin alike. Locked in a deadly embrace, the thunderous impact of Midgardsormr and the dreadnought Agrius tolled their mutual demise.Even now, the carcass of the immense wyrm lies entwined with the wreckage of the Agrius in the center of the lake.

In the central region of Abalathia's Spine, that great mountain range that spans Aldenard from east to west, can be found the forbidding highlands of Coerthas and the Holy See of Ishgard. Ishgard's formidable army of knights wages constant battle against its mortal enemies, the dragons. The legendary Dragoon has its roots in Ishgard, as it was here that their fighting style was developed.

The Dravanian hinterlands sit in the westernmost reaches of Abalathia's Spine, blessed with relatively lush vegetation due to waters carried through the area by the mighty Thaliak River. The region attained some fame as the seat of Sharlayan's colony, but this has faded in the fifteen years since the exodus. The settlement itself now largely stands unoccupied, a remnant of a lost time slowly being reclaimed by the land.

Abalathia's Spine (sometimes shortened to just Abalathia) is a great mountain range in Final Fantasy XIV. Spanning the northern end of the continent of Aldenard from east to west, much of it remained inaccessible until the development of airship travel.

fields.name: Summerford Farms
fields.description: The Summerford Farms are located high above and a short chocobo ride from the ocean and easily accessible from the Upper Decks of Limsa Lominsa. Supplying the capital city their produce, their hopsitable inn is well received by adventurers, though the bandit camps nearby pose more threats to the farms than the myriad of bite-sized beasties in the vacinity.

fields.name: Ul'Dah - Steps of Nald
fields.description: The western part of Ul'dah, the Steps of Nald follow the curve of the outer city. At its center lies a busy street lines with shops, temples, and inns. With throngs of people wandering in at all times of day, the area is forever alive with the sounds of trade and conversation.

fields.name: Horizon
fields.description: Along the Royal Allagan Sunway that connects Vesper Bay to Ul'dah, Horizon is home to a Brass Blades encampment there to ensure travelers and traders may pass safely between the harbors of Vesper Bay and Ul'dah proper. One can catch the first glimpse of dawn through Sunrise Gate to the east, and watch dusk fall through Sunset Gate to the west.

fields.name: Mor Dhona
fields.description: Alongside the shores of Silvertear Lake, Mor Dhona lies very close to the center of Aldenard. As a key land route blessed with breathtaking scenery, the area once featured a lively collection of inns. During the Battle of Silvertear Skies, however, an extreme aetherial surge swept through the landscape transforming much of it into pure crystal. Though the cause remains a topic of discussion amongst scholars, the phenomenon was indisputably destructive, and now the place is a wasteland shrouded in mephitic mists.

fields.name: Black Brush Station
fields.description: A marvel of modem innovation, the steam engine has transformed the mining industry, increasing efficiency and profits thrice over. I t has also led to the transformation of what was once a thinly manned aetheryte outpost into a thriving crossroads of labor and commerce - a new pillar to support the thriving Ul'dahn economy.

fields.name: Camp Drybone
fields.description: Situated along the Royal Allagan Sunway connecting Ul'dah with Gridania, Camp Drybone sits perilously close to Amalj'aa territory. As such, it is home to a great host of Immortal Flames, who are ever on alert for beastman attacks.

fields.name: Forgotten Springs
fields.description: In this village dwells the U tribe of Miqo'te, who live on water from the oasis and game from the Sagolii Desert. In times past, it was a stop for traders on the road to Cape Deadwind, the southernmost point of Aldenard. After continued pirate attacks sent the coastal area into decline, however, fewer and fewer travelers passed through the Springs, and now Ul'dah has all but forgotten it exists.

fields.name: Little Ala Mhigo
fields.description: Rejected bu the elementals of the Twelveswood and unable to adapt to Ul'dahn custom, Ala Mhigan refugees eventually settled in southern Thanalan. In exchange for supplies, the residents allow the Immortal Flames to maintain a presence, and Little Ala Mhigo now serves as a post whence to watch the movements of the Amalj'aa.

fields.name: Camp Bluefog
fields.description: Camp Bluefog was built as a post whence armed men could patrol the Ceruleum Field. Originally, this duty fell to the Brass Blades and Stone Torches. With the Empire's forces a mere stone's throw away, however, the Immortal Flames have since taken command.

fields.name: Ceruleum Processing Plant
fields.description: Operated by Amajina & Sons Mineral Concern, this plant refines raw ceruleum into a fuel for engines and other modern machinery. The Immortal Flames keep a heavy contingent of soldiers on hand to ensure that the facility and its precious product do not fall into enemy hands.

fields.name: The Gold Saucer
fields.description: An amusement park located at Southern Thanalan, founded and managed by the master goldsmith Godbert Manderville. It has a Cactuar known as "Senor Sabotender" as the official mascot of the park. Players can participate in different minigames such as the Triple Triad, Chocobo Racing, and many more to obtain a special currency known as MGP (Manderville Gold Saucer Points), which can be used to buy exclusive rewards in the park.

fields.name: The Goblet
fields.description: This is the residential section of Thanalan, where people can snatch up luxurious properties in order to make a base for themselves ofrtheir Free-Company.

fields.name: Helix
fields.description: A massive port of sorts that stands among the wastes of Azys Lla. According to a guidance node discovered near the ancient construct, it was one of the few imperial landings massive enough to house Ragnarok-class internment hulks. It would seem the docking rings that remain are but a fraction of those that stood in bygone days.
